    "faq_4xVCtD": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "text_zQtNUH": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can Mad Honey Overdose Kill you?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, mad honey can kill you, if you neglect the dosage guidelines, get intoxicated and fail to seek medical attention when necessary.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "text_9nkE9p": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can mad honey poisoning treatment be done at home?",
            "answer": "<p>If the effects are simple and minor, taking rest can simply flush the Grayanotoxin but if the case is severe you must seek medical help immediately. It is not recommended to try home remedy but rush for medical care for cases of mad honey poisoning. <br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "text_7Pri9j": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will Mad Honey Soaps and Balms intoxicate me?",
            "answer": "<p>No, products like Mad Honey Soap and Mad Honey Lip Balms don’t affect like the Mad Honey itself. You are free to use such products, without fear in Nepal.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_Ubdfzy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will mad honey affect my cats and dogs?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, mad honey is toxic to cats and dogs and should be kept far away from them. If accidental ingestion occurs, seek emergency veterinary care immediately.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
